of Java. I installed the latest from Sun (1.5_05), and changed the -vm arguments

configuration issue with my computer, and not a bug in the Eclipse release, but
I'm not sure what to do to fix it. I'm downloading 3.2M2 now, in the hopws that
will fix it; if it doesn't, how do you suggest I go about resolving this?

it is no longer broken. Sorry to have bothered you; I didn't actually think the
update would fix it.
